    All Classes and Interfaces

    Class
    Description
    AttributeViewer
    A front-end panel component that displays a collection of scheduling and runtime attributes related to the currently selected job, task, and core in the real-time simulation environment.
    BATS
    Blocking-Aware Two Speed implementation of Dynamic Voltage and Frequency Scaling Method.
    BF
    Best-Fit partitioning implementation.
    BFD
    Best-Fit Decreasing partitioning algorithm implementation.
    BS
    Base Speed implementation of Dynamic Voltage and Frequency Scaling Method.
    BTS
    Blocking-Time Stealing implementation of Dynamic Voltage and Frequency Scaling Method.
    ConcurrencyController
    Manages concurrency control operations for a processor.
    ConcurrencyControlProtocol
    Abstract base class for concurrency control protocols.
    Core
    Represents a single processing core in the simulator.
    CoreSet
    A set of cores that share speed/power configuration and belong to a processor.
    CoreSpeed
    Represents the operating speed and power consumption of a processing core at a specific operating point (for example, a DVFS level).
    CoreSpeedSet
    Collection of DVFS (Dynamic Voltage and Frequency Scaling) operating points for a core group.
    CoreTimeLine
    Visual timeline model for a single core used by the backâ€‘end UI renderer.
    Cost
    Represents a scheduling-related cost (delay) that affects a core while a requested job or migration is being processed.
    CriticalityLevel
    Represents a qualitative criticality level used in the workload model.
    CriticalSection
    Represents a critical section usage within a task's job.
    CriticalSectionSet
    Container of critical sections belonging to tasks within a workload.
    CSMS
    Critical Section Maximum Speed implementation of Dynamic Voltage and Frequency Scaling Method.
    DataReader
    Reads simulator configuration from XML and builds an in-memory DataSetting.
    DataSetting
    Aggregates fundamental simulation data structures: a processor, task set, and shared resource set.
    Definition
    Central definitions and constants used across the RTSimulator project.
    Definition.CoreStatus
    Enumeration of possible core statuses used by the simulator to represent a CPU core's current condition.
    Definition.DVFSType
    Enumeration of Dynamic Voltage and Frequency Scaling (DVFS) types.
    Definition.JobStatus
    Enumeration of possible job statuses during execution.
    Definition.PriorityType
    Enumeration of priority assignment types.
    Definition.SchedulingType
    Enumeration of scheduling algorithm types.
    DMS
    The Deadline Monotonic Scheduling Algorithm (DMS).
    DPCP
    Dynamic Priority Ceiling Protocol (DPCP) implementation.
    DUAL
    Dual Speed implementation of Dynamic Voltage and Frequency Scaling Method.
    DynamicVoltageAndFrequencyScalingMethod
    Abstract base class for dynamic voltage and frequency scaling methods.
    DynamicVoltageRegulator
    Dynamic Voltage Regulator facade that coordinates DVFS-related events.
    EDF
    The Earliest-Deadline-First scheduling algorithm (EDF).
    FCFS
    The First-Come First-Served scheduling algorithm (FCFS).
    FF
    First-Fit partitioning algorithm implementation.
    FFD
    First\-Fit Decreasing partitioning algorithm implementation.
    G_FMLP
     
    GDMS
    The Global Deadline Monotonic Scheduling Algorithm (GDMS).
    GEDF
    Global Earliest Deadline First Scheduling Algorithm (GEDF).
    GlobalSchedulingAlgorithm
    Abstract base class for global scheduling algorithms.
    GRMS
    Global Rate Monotonic Scheduling Algorithm (GRMS).
    HybridSchedulingAlgorithm
    Abstract base class for hybrid scheduling algorithms.
    InfoWin
    InfoWin is a small control panel and container used by the user interface to display and manage simulation result viewers and timeline controls.
    Job
    Represents an executable Job derived from a Task in the workload.
    JobQueue
    Priority queue of jobs ordered according to their natural ordering (as defined in Job).
    LST
    Least Slack Time Scheduling Algorithm (LST).
    MaxSpeed
    Max Speed implementation of Dynamic Voltage and Frequency Scaling Method.
    MissDeadlineInfo
    Encapsulates information about a missed deadline detected during the simulation.
    MouseStatus
    Tracks the current mouse interaction status used by the back-end viewer.
    MouseTimeLine
    Lightweight overlay component representing a selectable time marker (or interval highlight) associated with a specific SchedulingInfo on a timeline.
    MrsP
    Multiprocessor Resource Sharing Protocol (MrsP) implementation.
    MSRP
    Multiprocessor Stack Resource Policy (MSRP) implementation.
    Nest
    A simple container representing a collection of nested critical sections that belong to a Task.
    None
    No concurrency control protocol implementation.
    None
    None implementation of Dynamic Voltage and Frequency Scaling Method.
    None
    A partition algorithm implementation that performs no partitioning.
    NPCS
    Non-Preemptible Critical Section concurrency control protocol.
    OPA
    Optimal Priority Assignment (OPA) for single-core systems.
    P_FMLP
     
    PartitionAlgorithm
    Abstract base class for partition algorithms used to allocate tasks to cores.
    PartitionDistributor
    Distributes tasks across processor cores using a pluggable partition algorithm.
    PartitionedSchedulingAlgorithm
    Abstract base class for partitioned scheduling algorithms.
    PCP
    Priority Ceiling Protocol (PCP) implementation.
    PDMS
    Partitioned implementation of the DMS scheduler.
    PEDF
    Partitioned EDF scheduling algorithm implementation.
    PFCFS
    Partitioned implementation of the FCFS scheduler.
    PIP
    Priority Inheritance Protocol (PIP) implementation.
    PLST
    Partitioned implementation of the LST scheduler.
    Priority
    Priority class represents a priority value for scheduling tasks.
    PriorityDrivenSchedulingAlgorithm
    Base class for all priority-driven scheduling algorithms.
    PriorityLevel
    Represents a simple priority level for a task.
    PRMS
    Partitioned RMS scheduling algorithm implementation.
    Processor
    Central coordinator for the real-time simulator that owns cores, core sets, the global scheduler, concurrency controller, DVFS regulator and the task and resource sets.
    Resource
    Represents a single physical (or logical) resource instance managed by a SharedResource pool.
    ResourcePanel
    Swing panel representing a single shared resource instance accessed within a CriticalSection on the scheduling timeline.
    ResultSet
    Container for simulation result data.
    ResultViewer
    Scrollable container that hosts timeline visualization panels for scheduling results.
    RMS
    Rate Monotonic Scheduling Algorithm (RMS).
    RTSimulator
    Main class for RTSimulator application.
    RTSimulatorMath
    Utility class for performing mathematical operations used in the RTSimulator.
    SBP
    Similarity\-Based Partitioning (SBP) algorithm implementation.
    Scheduler
    Facade over a priority-driven scheduling algorithm for either a global or a local scheduler.
    ScheduleResult
    Builds and holds the processed scheduling timeline data for visualization.
    SchedulingInfo
    Represents scheduling information for a core at a specific time period.
    SciptToolBar
    A toolbar used by the ScriptSetter UI that provides quick actions to manage script groups and scripts and to start script execution.
    Script
    Represents a saved simulation script and its accumulated results.
    ScriptPanel
    A panel that builds and manages the UI used to configure a script for the application.
    ScriptResult
    Represents the results produced by executing a Script.
    ScriptRunnable
    A Runnable that executes a single script workload run.
    ScriptSetter
    Window and controller for creating and running script groups of simulations.
    ScriptTable
    A table panel for displaying and managing script information.
    SharedResource
    Represents a pool of identical resources that can be locked by Jobs.
    SharedResourceSet
    Typed collection of shared resources used for synchronization among tasks.
    SimulationResultPopupWin
    A popup window that displays summary statistics and configuration information for the current simulation run.
    SimulationViewer
    Main viewer panel that controls simulation setup, execution and result exporting within the front-end UI.
    Simulator
    Top-level simulation orchestrator that ties together the Processor, workload/resource settings and result collection.
    SingleCoreSchedulingAlgorithm
    Represents an abstract scheduling algorithm designed for single-core systems.
    SMC
    Static Mixed Criticality (SMC) scheduling algorithm.
    SRP
    Stack Resource Policy (SRP) concurrency control protocol.
    Task
    Represents a periodic or sporadic workload Task in the simulator.
    TaskExecution
    Immutable-like data carrier describing one contiguous execution-related interval for a task/job on a core, or a deadline miss marker.
    TaskSet
    Collection of tasks participating in the workload.
    TaskTimeLine
    Timeline renderer for a single Task used by the back-end visualization.
    TimeLineResult
    Timeline canvas panel that renders either core-centric or task-centric scheduling results and supports interactive markers and attribute probing.
    UserInterface
    UserInterface
    ViewerStatus
    Defines the runtime status of a UI viewer component in the back-end layer.
    WF
    Worst\-Fit partitioning algorithm implementation.
    WFD
    Worst-Fit Decreasing (WFD) partitioning algorithm implementation.
    wgCriticalSection
    Represents a generated critical section inside a workload task's job.
    wgCriticalSectionSet
    A collection of generated critical sections for a workload task.
    wgMath
    Small numeric utility helpers used by the workload generator.
    wgResource
    Represents a single resource entry used by the workload generator.
    wgResources
    Represents a group of identical resources and metadata used by the workload generator (for example, a resource pool with a quantity).
    wgResourcesSet
    Container for multiple wgResources groups used by the workload generator.
    wgTask
    Generator representation of a workload Task used by the workload generator.
    wgTaskSet
    A collection of generator tasks used by the workload generator.
    wgWorkload
     
    WorkloadGenerator
    Swing-based generator window for creating synthetic real-time workloads.
    XMLWriter
    Utility class for writing XML documents.
    XMLWriter
    Utility to build an XML DOM document that represents a generated workload.
